This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it proposes a novel neural network model for statistical machine translation that learns phrase representations. Additionally, the paper discusses the semantic and syntactic meaningfulness of the learned representations, which is a common topic in the field of natural language processing. 

The paper also involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed model in improving the existing log-linear model, which involves optimization and probability theory, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper mentions the use of the proposed model in image captioning, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
